page.title: 01North Wootton Castle Rising
page.content: This is the main heart of the 2 villages of North Wootton and Castle Rising which are divided by an area of woodland nown as Ling Common. Castle Rising is dominated by the Norman Castle and is a conservation area with very limited housing development. north Wootton is a village with large private housing estates which have developed since the late 1960's. Most of the people living in the area travel the short distance into the town of Kings Lynn to work. Both villages have attractive centres with a village green etc. Babingly in the North east is a very small farming community.
